"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM Examination\nJOIN Laboratory ON Examination.ID = Laboratory.ID\nWHERE `Examination Date` > '1997-01-01' AND APTT < 45;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of examinations done after January 1, 1997, where the activated partial prothrombin time (APTT) is within the normal range (less than 45). The query joins the `Examination` and `Laboratory` tables using the `ID` column, which is a foreign key relationship."